    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Note that there is a difference between a cast to <code>long</code> and a cast to <code>Long</code>. If you cast to <code>long</code> (a primitive value) then it should be automatically boxed to a <code>Long</code> (the reference type that wraps it).</p>\n\n<p>You could alternatively use <code>new</code> to create an instance of <code>Long</code>, initializing it with the <code>int</code> value.</p>\n"
  }, {
