      "comment_id" : 9611854,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "if <code>jPaidCountSpinner.getValue()</code> returns an Object that is in fact a <code>Long</code>, you definitely only need to put a <code>(Long)</code> cast in front. Also try putting a breakpoint on your check for <code>int.class</code> or <code>long.class</code> etc. Does it ever hit it? And if you have a number-like object, it will support <code>java.util.Number</code>, so cast it to that and call the <code>longValue</code> method. No need to go via a string in that case. So this function could be simplified quite a bit, even if you also need to deal with strings. (Part of the problem here is the bad reference documentation for <code>JSpinner</code>)."
