    "question_id" : 1302605,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Java you can do:</p>\n\n<pre><code> int myInt=4;\n Long myLong= new Long(myInt);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>in your case it would be: </p>\n\n<pre><code>content.setSequence(new Long(i));\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1632148,
      "reputation" : 12107,
      "user_id" : 1506477,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 100,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a5d48d8856ee5051fbb431cd0cf12deb?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "TG Gowda",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1506477/tg-gowda"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1425981795,
    "creation_date" : 1425981795,
    "answer_id" : 28960761,
    "question_id" : 1302605,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>We shall get the long value by using <code>Number</code> reference.</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static long toLong(Number number){\n    return number.longValue();\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>It works for all number types, here is a test:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static void testToLong() throws Exception {\n    assertEquals(0l, toLong(0));   // an int\n    assertEquals(0l, toLong((short)0)); // a short\n    assertEquals(0l, toLong(0l)); // a long\n    assertEquals(0l, toLong((long) 0)); // another long\n    assertEquals(0l, toLong(0.0f));  // a float\n    assertEquals(0l, toLong(0.0));  // a double\n\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5534765,
      "reputation" : 420,
      "user_id" : 4393496,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fe2b373d8e975cb3b309c8892932ac7f?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Mohammadreza Tavakoli",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4393496/mohammadreza-tavakoli"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 20,
    "last_activity_date" : 1459606236,
    "creation_date" : 1459606236,
    "answer_id" : 36374325,
    "question_id" : 1302605,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>use <br></p>\n\n<pre><code>new Long(your_integer);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>or</p>\n\n<pre><code>Long.valueOf(your_integer);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6593416,
      "reputation" : 29545,
      "user_id" : 5093961,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3736a281ed5cdc18e41f6d3100d76dcc?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Steven Spungin",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5093961/steven-spungin"
